1
00:00:00,250 --> 00:00:04,250
This was the group cell, which
was all divided but later dismantled

2
00:00:04,958 --> 00:00:07,208
There was a ventilation opening here

3
00:00:07,708 --> 00:00:14,750
Sometimes they would fire bullets
through the opening to break our spirits

4
00:00:16,083 --> 00:00:18,208
Here, there used to be a door

5
00:00:20,083 --> 00:00:26,250
There was a door here. Sometimes we
stood and saw a faint light in the corridor

6
00:00:26,291 --> 00:00:29,458
Because in the end, we only ever saw the jailers

7
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:31,625
Everyone here wrote his memories

8
00:00:32,125 --> 00:00:34,958
Then they repainted the prison

9
00:00:36,041 --> 00:00:40,541
But later new prisoners came and wrote new memories again

10
00:00:53,791 --> 00:00:58,166
Very few

11
00:00:58,166 --> 00:00:59,916
Witness: At first, they gave a little... Interviewer:
Read us something that was written on the wall

12
00:01:00,416 --> 00:01:06,375
For example, it says, Do not lose heart or
grieve, for you are superior if you are believers
